    "Their study reveals that through data with maximal educational value, it is feasible to achieve substantial reductions in the size of language models for code-related tasks.",
    "Similarly, Li et al. [24] have investigated the impact of dataset selection strategies on models designed for commonsense reasoning.",
    "Recently, Surkov and Yamshchikov [25] introduced ''Vygotsky distance'', a tool for benchmark similarity assessment that could potentially structure further choices of training data and benchmarks to maximize generalization potential of the models.",
